\section{Computing genome complexity}
\label{sec:comp-genome-compl}

% \lettrine[lines=4, slope=-0.5em, lhang=0.5, findent=2.1em, nindent=-0.9em, loversize=0.25]{A}{mong}
Among 20 major systematic groups we pick 54 species and computed the complexity value (CV) of their genomes with sizes ranging from 3.4Gb to 1.6Kb \autoref{tab:genome}. The first striking observation was the degree of direct correlation observed between genome size and CV (\fref{fig:gen_compl}{-A}) with a slope of the regression equal to 0.967. This first result implies a maximum complexity for all genomes. The residual variation around the fitted regression and along the 6 orders of magnitude, was almost null ($adjusted-R^{2} = 0.987$).

